hijackers showed no physical or verbal violent intentions and 
made no statements about their motives 
algeria has long experience in negotiating the release of 
hostages most recently in april 1988 when mediators won the 
freedom of 31 hostages aboard a hijacked kuwait airways jet 
western officials criticized algeria for releasing the 
hijackers who killed two people 
algerian diplomats played a key role in winning the 1981 release 
of americans held hostage at the us embassy in iran they also 
brokered the release of many western hostages in lebanon 
