a gangs plot to murder police officers on 
new years eve has been foiled by the arrests of three young men 
and seizure of weapons police said 
the alleged plot apparently was in retaliation for police 
crackdowns on gangcontrolled drug operations in the van nuys and 
sylmar areas of the san fernando valley said lt jim vojtecky 
as early as september we began getting inforamtion that local 
street gangs were getting a little irritated and we had 
indications they were going to attempt to kill a cop because we 
were screwing up their drug operations in the streets vojtecky 
said 
gang violence in the nations secondlargest city reached record 
levels during 1990 as of nov 30 gang violence had accounted for 
315 deaths in 1990 a 124 percent jump over 1989 when 303 people 
died in gang attacks 
vojtecky said tension between police and gangs in the van nuys 
area has been building for months recent information from 
informants convinced police that an attempt to kill police would be 
made on new years eve vojtecky said 
in early morning raids saturday police seized two rifles one 
with a sawedoff barrel one handgun and 163 rounds of ammunition 
sergio camarena cesar reveles and hector aleman all 18 were 
taken into custody camarena and reveles were booked for 
investigation of conspiracy to commit murder and aleman was booked 
for possession of a sawedoff rifle 
the three belonged to the same gang which vojtecky declined to 
identify in keeping with departmental policy designed to avoid 
giving publicity to individual gangs 
vojtecky said officers did not have time to determine how the 
alleged murder plot was to be carried out 
police believe the plot was foiled by the arrests however a 
bulletin was issued advising officers throughout los angeles to be 
careful on new years eve 
saturdays arrests followed by hours a spate of gang violence in 
the region that left a 13yearold boy dead and a girl critically 
wounded 
the 13yearold boy was shot while sleeping in the living room 
of his grandmothers home in suburban pomona police said the 
gunman apparently mistook the youth visiting from claremont for a 
member of a local gang 
the girl was shot in the head when several rounds were fired 
through the living room window of her home in southwest los 
angeles the 13yearold was listed in very critical condition at 
cedarsinai medical center 
police lt joe germain said investigators suspect it was gang 
gunfire but did not know if the girl was the intended victim 
