a strong earthquake rocked tokyo and its 
neighboring area monday morning the central meteorological agency 
said 
there were no immediate reports of damage or casualties from the 
805 am tremor police said 
the earthquake had a preliminary reading of 51 on the richter 
scale said the meteorological agency it was centered in the 
eastern part of chiba prefecture a state on the eastern border of 
tokyo 
the earthquake also registered 3 on the japanese scale of 7 in 
katsuura and tateyama two coastal cities in the state it was 
strong enough to overturn unfastened objects 
the richter scale is a gauge of the strength of an earthquake as 
measured by the ground motion recorded on a seismograph a quake 
measuring 5 on the scale can cause considerable damage 
the japanese scale measures the intensity of an earthquake at a 
particular location it is not convertible to the richter scale 
