thirtyseven members of an albanian jewish 
family on sunday became the first jews to be allowed to leave 
albania under a deal secretly negotiated with the communist 
government an american jewish group said 
on a flight dubbed the flying carpet the family left the 
albanian capital of tirana on sunday headed for israel via rome 
said shula bahat a spokeswoman for the american jewish committee 
this is going to save albanian jews from total extinction 
said the groups foreign relations consultant rabbi marc 
tanenbaum had they remained there they would have been wiped 
out in a generation 
in rome the family was aided by the italian government and 
representatives of the jerusalembased jewish agency bahat said 
further details about the family were not immediately known 
the jewish agency which is financing the resettlement of 
albanian jews negotiated in secret with the albanian israeli and 
italian governments to facilitate the immigration she said 
the familys departure forged the way to the west for albanias 
500 jews most of whom are expected to leave the repressive country 
after decades of being cut off from the world jewish community she 
said 
sundays flight as well as future flights to the west for 
albanias jews has been nicknamed the flying carpet bahat 
said 
she said jews have not been allowed to practice their religion 
by albanias government one of the last in eastern europe to 
maintain a political hard line as surrounding countries turned to 
democracy 
